{
  "texts": [
    "• Perception System Errors: Sensor inaccuracies (e.g., misdetecting a fragile vase as sturdy) can lead to unsafe grasps or collisions, especially in cluttered spaces like offices.",
    "These challenges translate to three technical sub-problems:• Real-Time Validation: Task plans must adapt dynamically to environmental changes (e.g., object fragility updates) to prevent unsafe actions.",
    "• Fast Graph Retrieval: Rapid access to environmental data (e.g., obstacle positions) is critical for real-time safety compliance.",
    "• Logical Reasoning: Task plans must align with physical constraints (e.g., force limits, spatial relationships) even in dynamic scenarios.",
    "Our framework addresses these sub-problems through Embodied Robotic Control Prompts (ERCPs) for resolving ambiguities, an Embodied Knowledge Graph (EKG) for real-time validation, and Graph Attention Networks (GATs) with Hamiltonian Paths to prioritize critical constraints and optimize task sequencing."
  ]
}